description:
Add tokens, AST nodes, parser cases, and evaluators for 6 new conditions: burn_rate, model contains, context_size, context_usage, error_type, task_status.

Spec: private/rev-2-specs/SPEC-02-hook-engine-update.md sections 4.1-4.6
Existing code: internal/dsl/tokens.go, internal/dsl/ast.go, internal/dsl/parser.go, internal/engine/conditions.go
Shared dep: internal/metrics/ (for BurnRate — from Wave 0)

Key implementation note: Do NOT add 'model' to the keywords map (collision risk). Pattern-match on TokenIdent value in the parser. Same for burn_rate, context_size, context_usage, error_type, task_status.

Acceptance criteria (from SPEC-02 section 9, item 4):
- 'if burn_rate > 0.8' parses to BurnRateCondition{Op: '>', Threshold: 0.8}
- 'if model contains "opus"' parses to ModelCondition{Substring: 'opus'}
- 'if context_size > 100000' parses to ContextSizeCondition{Op: '>', Threshold: 100000}
- 'if error_type == "rate_limit"' parses to FieldEqCondition{Field: 'error_type', Value: 'rate_limit'}
- 'if task_status == "completed"' parses to FieldEqCondition{Field: 'task_status', Value: 'completed'}
- 'if context_usage > 80' parses to ContextUsageCondition{Op: '>', Threshold: 80.0}
- All existing parser and condition tests pass
- go test ./internal/dsl/... ./internal/engine/... passes

Testing standard: Read docs/testing.md
